class CustomExtender(DomainExtender):
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def initialize(self): """Perform initialization""" pass
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def validate(self): """Perform validation""" pass
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addInitialDomainFeatures(self): """Add initial domain features when the domain is in offline mode""" pass
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addOfflineDomainFeatures(self): """Add additional domain features when the domain is in offline mode""" pass

base.log('Adding foregin JNDI for OSB Cluster') cd('/Clusters/OsbCluster') hosts=[] servers=cmo.getServers() for server in servers: hosts.append(server.getMachine().getName()+":"+str(server.getListenPort()))
cd('/') cmo.createForeignJNDIProvider('ForeignJNDIProvider')
cd('/ForeignJNDIProviders/ForeignJNDIProvider') set('Targets',jarray.array([ObjectName('com.bea:Name=AppCluster,Type=Cluster')], ObjectName)) cmo.setInitialContextFactory('weblogic.jndi.WLInitialContextFactory')
urls='t3://' i=false for host in hosts: if i: urls=urls+',' urls=urls+host i=true base.log('Setting provider urls: '+urls) cmo.setProviderURL(urls) cmo.createForeignJNDILink('ForeignJNDILink')
cd('/ForeignJNDIProviders/ForeignJNDIProvider/ForeignJNDILinks/ForeignJNDILink') cmo.setLocalJNDIName('getBankingDateToTM#com.nordea.ejb.DateControlRemote') cmo.setRemoteJNDIName('getBankingDateToTM#com.nordea.ejb.DateControlRemote')
base.log('Unset CBCDataEvent-FS JNDIPropertiesCredentialEncrypted') try: cd('/JMSSystemResources/CBCDataEvent-module/JMSResource/CBCDataEvent-module/ForeignServers/CBCDataEvent-FS') cmo.unSet('JNDIPropertiesCredentialEncrypted') except: base.log('ForeignServer CBCDataEvent-FS not found, skipping') dumpStack() exit(exitcode=10)
base.log('Create JNDI Properties datasource=jdbc/CBPDRSDataSource for the foreign server CBCDataEvent-FS') try: cmo.createJNDIProperty('datasource') cd('/JMSSystemResources/CBCDataEvent-module/JMSResource/CBCDataEvent-module/ForeignServers/CBCDataEvent-FS/JNDIProperties/datasource') cmo.setValue('jdbc/CBPDRSDataSource') except: base.log('Failed to create JNDI datasource=jdbc/CBPDRSDataSource for the foreign server CBCDataEvent-FS') dumpStack() exit(exitcode=10) base.log('CBTEC-26161 Add IgnoreStuckThreads') cd('/') domainN=cmo.getName() workMgrsNames = ["CreateBookingRequestPollExecutorWM", "CreateBookingReplyPollExecutorWM", "ValidateBookingReplyPollExecutorWM", "CreateBookingHVLPRequestPollExecutorWM", "CreateBookingHVLPReplyPollExecutorWM", "ValidateBookingHVLPReplyPollExecutorWM"] for wm in workMgrsNames: try: base.log('Set IgnoreStuckThreads for:'+wm) cd('/SelfTuning/'+domainN+'/WorkManagers/'+wm) cmo.setIgnoreStuckThreads(true) except: base.log('IgnoreStuckThreads failed for:'+wm) dumpStack() exit(exitcode=10)
base.log('CBTEC-40242 Change SBDefaultResponseWorkManager') rtSPDefault='ResponseTimeRequestClass-SBDefaultResponseWorkManager' minSPDefault='MinThreadsConstraint-SBDefaultResponseWorkManager' cd('/SelfTuning/'+domainN) try: cmo.createResponseTimeRequestClass(rtSPDefault) base.log(rtSPDefault+' created') except: base.log(rtSPDefault+' alredy exist. Ignoring ..') try: cd('/SelfTuning/'+domainN+'/MinThreadsConstraints/'+minSPDefault) cmo.setCount(20) base.log(minSPDefault+' change completed') cd('/SelfTuning/'+domainN+'/ResponseTimeRequestClasses/'+rtSPDefault) set('Targets',jarray.array([ObjectName('com.bea:Name=OsbCluster,Type=Cluster')], ObjectName)) cmo.setGoalMs(0) cd('/SelfTuning/'+domainN+'/WorkManagers/SBDefaultResponseWorkManager') cmo.setResponseTimeRequestClass(getMBean('/SelfTuning/'+domainN+'/ResponseTimeRequestClasses/'+rtSPDefault)) base.log(rtSPDefault+' change completed') except: base.log(rtSPDefault+'/'+minSPDefault+' change failed') dumpStack() exit(exitcode=10)
base.log('CBTEC-47769 Disabling of diagnostic framework started') cd('/WLDFSystemResources/Module-FMWDFW/WLDFResource/Module-FMWDFW/WatchNotification/Module-FMWDFW/Watches/Deadlock') cmo.setEnabled(false)
cd('/WLDFSystemResources/Module-FMWDFW/WLDFResource/Module-FMWDFW/WatchNotification/Module-FMWDFW/Watches/HeapSpace') cmo.setEnabled(false)
cd('/WLDFSystemResources/Module-FMWDFW/WLDFResource/Module-FMWDFW/WatchNotification/Module-FMWDFW/Watches/StuckThread') cmo.setEnabled(false)
cd('/WLDFSystemResources/Module-FMWDFW/WLDFResource/Module-FMWDFW/WatchNotification/Module-FMWDFW/Watches/UncheckedException') cmo.setEnabled(false)
#cd('/WLDFSystemResources/Module-FMWDFW/WLDFResource/Module-FMWDFW/WatchNotification/Module-FMWDFW') #cmo.setEnabled(false) base.log('CBTEC-47769 Disabling of diagnostic framework finished')

print "\n=========================================================================" print "List of Proxy Services using: " + target.upper() print "========================================================================="
query.setServiceEnabled(true) allRefs = alsbCore.getRefs(query) for ref in allRefs: typeId = ref.getTypeId() if typeId == "ProxyService": if action == "disable": proxymbean.disableService(ref) print "[DISABLED] Proxy Service: " + ref.getFullName() if action == "status": print "[ENABLED] Proxy Service: " + ref.getFullName()
query.setServiceEnabled(false) allRefs = alsbCore.getRefs(query) for ref in allRefs: typeId = ref.getTypeId() if typeId == "ProxyService": if action == "enable": proxymbean.enableService(ref) print "[ENABLED] Proxy Service: " + ref.getFullName() if action == "status": print "[DISABLED] Proxy Service: " + ref.getFullName()
print "\n=========================================================================" print "List of Business Services using: " + target.upper() print "========================================================================="
bsQuery.setServiceEnabled(true) allRefs = alsbCore.getRefs(bsQuery) for ref in allRefs: typeId = ref.getTypeId() if typeId == "BusinessService": if action == "disable": businessmbean.disableService(ref) print "[DISABLED] Business Service: " + ref.getFullName() if action == "status": print "[ENABLED] Business Service: " + ref.getFullName()
bsQuery.setServiceEnabled(false) allRefs = alsbCore.getRefs(bsQuery) for ref in allRefs: typeId = ref.getTypeId() if typeId == "BusinessService": if action == "enable": businessmbean.enableService(ref) print "[ENABLED] Business Service: " + ref.getFullName() if action == "status": print "[DISABLED] Business Service: " + ref.getFullName()

if action not in action_list: print "ERROR: Allowed action: status|enable|disable" sys.exit(1)
if target not in target_list: print "ERROR: Allowed target: all|mq|kafka|jca" sys.exit(1)
print "--------Status//Enable//Disable Service Endpoints script --------------"
execfile( 'scripts/standard.py' ) standardDomain.initialize() control.connectAdmin()
domName=cmo.getName() domainRuntime()
print "=== sessionMBean ===" sessionMBean = findService(SessionManagementMBean.NAME,SessionManagementMBean.TYPE) sessionName="WLSTSession"+ str(System.currentTimeMillis()) if action == "enable" or action == "disable": sessionMBean.createSession(sessionName) print "=== alsbSession ===" alsbSession = findService(ALSBConfigurationMBean.NAME + "." + sessionName, ALSBConfigurationMBean.TYPE) print "=== alsbCore ===" alsbCore = findService(ALSBConfigurationMBean.NAME, ALSBConfigurationMBean.TYPE) proxymbean = findService(String("ProxyServiceConfiguration.").concat(sessionName),'com.bea.wli.sb.management.configuration.ProxyServiceConfigurationMBean') businessmbean = findService(String("BusinessServiceConfiguration.").concat(sessionName),'com.bea.wli.sb.management.configuration.BusinessServiceConfigurationMBean') print "=== query ProxyServiceQuery ==="
if "mq" in target: serviceManagement("mq", action) if "kafka" in target: serviceManagement("kafka", action) if "jca" in target: serviceManagement("jca", action) if target == "all": serviceManagement("all", action)
if action == "disable" or action == "enable": print "Session activation ..." sessionMBean.activateSession(sessionName, "Action: " +action +", target: "+target+ " all proxy services") #activate osb session

# # JCA configuration # # Format: # # <serverid>=<url> # <url>=<protocol>://<host>[:<port>][?<param1>[&param2][&paramN]] # <protocol> = dci | tandem | otma | loadbalance # # === Supported protocols === # dci --> Connect to CICS DCI using SRIU5 protocol # tandem --> Connect to Tandem / HP Nonstop using proprietary socket protocol # otma --> Connect to IMS using OTMA protocol (IMS Connect) # loadbalance --> Loadbalance/failover between more than one server - servers are listed in <host> part of URL as <server1>-<server2>-<serverN> # # === URL Parameters === # # - General # userid --> UserID to use when communicating with the server # password --> Password # timeout --> Socket timeout in milliseconds # # Userid and Password can be obfuscated or encrypted using com.nordea.sc.jca.PasswordUtils # # - Loadbalancer related # pingservice --> Name of service to ping, used when checking if server is alive or not # inactiveperiod --> If the service is down, this is the number of seconds a service is marked down for until it is brought up again. # queryavailability --> Set to true or false, if true availability will be queried (polled). # failonerror --> If a service error occurs, should we mark the server as down or not ? # # - OTMA specific # datastore --> Name of IMS Datastore to connect to # persistent --> If true, the socket connection to the IMS will be reused for multiple requests, if false it will be closed after each request. # #
# Danish CICS backend DK=loadbalance://DK1-DK2?inactiveperiod=3600&failonerror=true DK1=dci://${DK_1_HOST_NAME}:${DK_1_PORT_NAME}?userid=${DK_USER_NAME}&password=${DK_USER_PASSWORD}&timeout=${DK_TCP_TIMEOUT}&codepage=cp277&queryavailability=true&failonerror=true&inactiveperiod=300 DK2=dci://${DK_2_HOST_NAME}:${DK_2_PORT_NAME}?userid=${DK_USER_NAME}&password=${DK_USER_PASSWORD}&timeout=${DK_TCP_TIMEOUT}&codepage=cp277&queryavailability=true&failonerror=true&inactiveperiod=300
# Sweden IMS backend SE=otma://${SE_HOST}:${SE_PORT}?datastore=${SE_DATASTORE}&userid=${SE_USER_NAME}&password=${SE_USER_PASSWORD}&persistent=false
# Norwegian IMS backend NO=otma://${NO_HOST_NAME}:${NO_PORT_NAME}?datastore=${NO_DATASTORE_NAME}&userid=${NO_USER_NAME}&password=${NO.password}&persistent=false
# Finish IMS and HP NonStop/Tandem backend tandemFI=loadbalance://tandemFIA-tandemFIB tandemFIA=tandem://${FI_1_TANDEM_HOST_NAME}:${FI_1_TANDEM_PORT_NAME}?userid=${FI_1_TANDEM_USER_NAME}&password=${FI_1_TANDEM_USER_PASSWORD} tandemFIB=tandem://${FI_2_TANDEM_HOST_NAME}:${FI_2_TANDEM_PORT_NAME}?userid=${FI_2_TANDEM_USER_NAME}&password=${FI_2_TANDEM_USER_PASSWORD} tandemFI2=tandem://${FI_3_TANDEM_HOST_NAME}:${FI_3_TANDEM_PORT_NAME}?userid=${FI_3_TANDEM_USER_NAME}&password=${FI_3_TANDEM_USER_PASSWORD} tandemFIPerf=tandem://${FI_3_TANDEM_HOST_NAME}:${FI_3_TANDEM_PORT_2_NAME}?userid=${FI_3_TANDEM_USER_NAME}&password=${FI_3_TANDEM_USER_PASSWORD} tandemFIPrioA=tandem://${FI_A_PRIO_TANDEM_HOST_NAME}:${FI_A_PRIO_TANDEM_PORT_NAME}?userid=${FI_A_PRIO_TANDEM_USER_NAME}&password=${FI_A_PRIO_TANDEM_USER_PASSWORD} tandemFIPrioB=tandem://${FI_B_PRIO_TANDEM_HOST_NAME}:${FI_B_PRIO_TANDEM_PORT_NAME}?userid=${FI_B_PRIO_TANDEM_USER_NAME}&password=${FI_B_PRIO_TANDEM_USER_PASSWORD} tandemFIPrio=loadbalance://tandemFIPrioA-tandemFIPrioB

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------- # OSB Coherence extender is added via the osb-extender.py #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- class CoherenceExtender(DomainExtender): #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def initialize(self): """Perform initialization""" pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def validate(self): """Perform validation""" pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addInitialDomainFeatures(self): """Add initial domain features when the domain is in offline mode""" #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addOfflineDomainFeatures(self): """Add domain features when the domain is in offline mode""" print 'Extended coherence configuration started in offline mode' print 'cleanup defaultCoherenceCluster...' cd('/') cd('/CoherenceClusterSystemResources') delete('defaultCoherenceCluster','CoherenceClusterSystemResource') print 'cleanup defaultCoherenceCluster completed' pass
def getCoherenceTargets(self): # Creates an empty collection of targets # If the Coherence target is a cluster, get the list of servers for this cluster and add them into the collection of targets # If the Coherence target is a server, add this server to the collection of clusters # Return the list of targets serverTargets = []
for coherence in standardDomain.project.resources.getCollection('CoherenceClusters'): cm = coherence.getValue('clustermode') #print 'DEBUG cm: ' + cm if cm == 'unicast': cn = coherence.getValue('name') #print 'DEBUG cn: ' + cn cd('/CoherenceClusterSystemResources/'+cn) listTargets = cmo.getTargets() #print 'DEBUG listTargets: ' + str(listTargets) for target in listTargets: if target.getType() == 'Cluster': #print 'DEBUG serverTargets in cluster branch: ' cd('/CoherenceClusterSystemResources/'+cn+'/Targets/'+target.getName()) serverTargets.extend(cmo.getServers()) elif target.getType() == 'Server': #print 'DEBUG serverTargets in server branch: ' serverTargets.append(target) return serverTargets
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addOnlineEditDomainFeatures(self): print 'Coherence NEW VERSION CBTEC-75446 online configuration started' # require Ninjago CoherenceClusters definitions : osbCoherenceCluster and wsmCoherenceCluster, unicast, port=8100/8110 in CaC ->Resources -> CoherenceClusters for coherence in standardDomain.project.resources.getCollection('CoherenceClusters'): cm = coherence.getValue('clustermode') if cm == 'unicast': cn = coherence.getValue('name') print 'configure '+cn+' unicast cluster' cd('/CoherenceClusterSystemResources/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterResource/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterParams/'+cn) cmo.setClusterListenPort(int(coherence.getValue('port')))
print 'configure WKAs' print '--- TARGETS:'
#cd('/CoherenceClusterSystemResources/'+cn+'/Targets')
ix = 1 wkas = [] mports = {}
serverTargets = self.getCoherenceTargets() if len(serverTargets)==0: print "The list of Coherence clusters is empty"
for i in serverTargets: print "Target name: " + i.getName() + " -- Target type: " + i.getType()
#for ms in ls('c', returnMap='true'): for ms in serverTargets: m = cfg.serverMachines[ms.getName()] ip = cfg.machineAdrs[m] port = int(coherence.getValue('port'))+1 if mports.has_key(m): port = mports[m] + 1 mports[m] = port print ms.getName()+':'+m+':'+ip if ip == m and cfg.networkSuffix is not None: ip = m+'.'+cfg.networkSuffix if ip not in wkas: wkas.append(ip) cd('/CoherenceClusterSystemResources/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterResource/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterParams/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterWellKnownAddresses/'+cn) cmo.createCoherenceClusterWellKnownAddress('WKA-'+str(ix)) cd('/CoherenceClusterSystemResources/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterResource/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterParams/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterWellKnownAddresses/'+cn+'/CoherenceClusterWellKnownAddresses/WKA-'+str(ix)) cmo.setListenAddress(ip) ix += 1 cd('/Servers/'+ms.getName()+'/CoherenceMemberConfig/'+ms.getName()) cmo.setUnicastListenPort(port) cmo.setUnicastListenAddress(ip) cmo.setUnicastPortAutoAdjust(true) print cn+' unicast cluster configured successfully' print 'Extended coherence configuration completed' pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addOnlineDomainFeatures(self): """Add domain features when the domain is in online and not in edit mode""" pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def cleanDomainResources(self, dir): """Following a cleanup, remove any additional files Args: dir: The domain directory, either local or remote """ pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def preDeploy(self,update): """Prepare deploy after all servers have been started before Args: update: true for update, false for install """ pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def deploy(self, deployment): """Deploy a specialized deployment Args: deployment: The deployment base object Returns: true if the deployment was handled, false if not """ return false #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def postDeploy(self,update): """Finalize deploy after all deployments have been done Args: update: true for update, false for install """ pass standardDomain.addExtender( CoherenceExtender() )

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addOfflineDomainFeatures(self): """Add additional domain features when the domain is in offline mode""" pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addOnlineEditDomainFeatures(self): """Add domain features when the domain is in online and edit mode""" base.log('Set minimum capacity for datasource mds-owsm') cd('/JDBCSystemResources/mds-owsm/JDBCResource/mds-owsm/JDBCConnectionPoolParams/mds-owsm') cmo.setMinCapacity(1) base.log('Set minimum capacity for datasource CBPDRSDataSource') cd('/JDBCSystemResources/CBPDRSDataSource/JDBCResource/CBPDRSDataSource/JDBCConnectionPoolParams/CBPDRSDataSource') cmo.setMinCapacity(4) #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def addOnlineDomainFeatures(self): """Add domain features when the domain is in online and not in edit mode""" pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def cleanDomainResources(self, dir): """Following a cleanup, remove any additional files Args: dir: The domain directory, either local or remote """ pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def preDeploy(self,update): """Prepare deploy after all servers have been started before Args: update: true for update, false for install """ pass #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def deploy(self, deployment): """Deploy a specialized deployment Args: deployment: The deployment base object Returns: true if the deployment was handled, false if not """ return false #----------------------------------------------------------------------------- def postDeploy(self,update): """Finalize deploy after all deployments have been done Args: update: true for update, false for install """ pass standardDomain.addExtender( OsbDataSourceExtender() )
